---DOM manipulation in JavaScript refers to the process of interacting with the 
Document Object Model (DOM) of an HTML document.DOM manipulation with JavaScript 
is commonly used in web development to create dynamic and interactive user interfaces.


--You can change the text, HTML, or attributes of elements based on user actions or other events.
--You can respond to user interactions, such as clicks, keypresses, and form submissions, by dynamically updating the DOM.
--Creating and Deleting Elements.
--Styling Changes.
--You can use DOM manipulation in conjunction with AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML) to fetch and display data from a server without requiring a full page reload
--You can create animations.
--Managing events and their associated actions is a key aspect of DOM manipulation.
--You can use DOM manipulation to validate form inputs and provide feedback to users without submitting the form.


Document object model: htmll ile css arasindaki bir arayuz.
Elementlere nesne olarak ulasabiliyoruz(DOM)

5 MAIN METHODS:
Document.GetElementById();
Document.GetElementByClassName();
Document.GetElementByTagName();
Document.querySelector();
document.getSelectorAll();


SELECT ISLEMI:

ex:
var tag = document.GetElementById();
var tagg = document.querySelector(`p`); //burda p tagi secilmis oldu.

MANIPULATE ISLEMI:

ex:
tag.style.colo = `blue`
tagg.textcontent // icerisini donduruyorum. textler icin!!
link.getAttribute(`href`); //icerigi degistirmek istersek  link.setAttribute(`href`,`www.abcd.com`)








